OL,3,CCities launch 'cool spaces' to escape
OL,4,Cthe heat - where can I find them?
OL,6,FBristol City Council launched a 'Keep
OL,7,FBristol Cool' mapping tool,
OL,8,Fresearching where it is most impacted
OL,9,Fby heat.
OL,11,FTheir website includes a list of
OL,12,Flibraries, community centres, and
OL,13,Freligious buildings that are open to
OL,14,Fthe public as cool spaces.
OL,16,FThe University of Gloucester is also
OL,17,Flaunching a Bristol Quiet Areas Plan,
OL,18,Fwhich includes a map listing "quiet,
OL,19,Faccessible, cool" spaces for
OL,20,Fneurodivergent adults and members of
OL,21,Fthe community.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
